overview: The user's primary intent was to enable external testing for a
  prefilling feature and to verify the functionality of the application's admin
  flow. For the prefilling feature, I identified that its visibility is
  controlled by the  environment variable. I
  provided clear steps for the user to set this variable in their Vercel project
  settings, making the prefill button accessible on deployed environments. For
  the admin flow, after understanding its components (login, dashboard, API
  routes, middleware), I performed a comprehensive manual test using the browser
  tool, as per the user's preference to avoid new Cypress tests. I successfully
  tested login with both incorrect and correct passwords, verified dashboard
  access, confirmed the responses API and CSV download functionality, and
  ensured logout and protected route redirection were working. The outcome is
  that both the prefilling feature can be enabled for testing, and the admin
  flow is fully verified and ready.
